label: crsUrn
comment:
A Uniform Resource Name (URN) for the coordinate reference system (crs) used to define 'Location.PositionPoints'.
An example would be the European Petroleum Survey Group (EPSG) code for a coordinate reference system, defined in URN under the Open Geospatial Consortium (OGC) namespace as: urn:ogc:def:crs:EPSG::XXXX, where XXXX is an EPSG code (a full list of codes can be found at the EPSG Registry web site http://www.epsg-registry.org/). To define the coordinate system as being WGS84 (latitude, longitude) using an EPSG OGC, this attribute would be urn:ogc:def:crs:EPSG::4236.
A profile should limit this code to a set of allowed URNs agreed to by all sending and receiving parties.

label: mRID
comment:
Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended.
For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

label: name
comment: The name is any free human readable and possibly non unique text naming the object.

label: mainAddress
comment: Main address of the location.

label: PowerSystemResources
comment: All power system resources at this location.

label: CoordinateSystem
comment: Coordinate system used to describe position points of this location.

label: xPosition
comment: X axis position.

label: zPosition
comment: (if applicable) Z axis position.

label: yPosition
comment: Y axis position.

label: sequenceNumber
comment: Zero-relative sequence number of this point within a series of points.

label: Location
comment: Location described by this position point.

label: reason
comment: Reason code or explanation for why an object went to the current status 'value'.

label: remark
comment: Pertinent information regarding the current 'value', as free form text.

label: value
comment: Status value at 'dateTime'; prior status changes may have been kept in instances of activity records associated with the object to which this status applies.

label: dateTime
comment: Date and time for which status 'value' applies.

label: townDetail
comment: Town detail.

label: postalCode
comment: Postal code for the address.

label: streetDetail
comment: Street detail.

label: language
comment: The language in which the address is specified, using ISO 639-1 two digit language code.

label: status
comment: Status of this address.

label: poBox
comment: Post office box.

label: code
comment: (if applicable) Utilities often make use of external reference systems, such as those of the town-planner's department or surveyor general's mapping system, that allocate global reference codes to streets.

label: suiteNumber
comment: Number of the apartment or suite.

label: floorIdentification
comment: The identification by name or number, expressed as text, of the floor in the building as part of this address.

label: suffix
comment: Suffix to the street name. For example: North, South, East, West.

label: name
comment: Name of the street.

label: withinTownLimits
comment: True if this street is within the legal geographical boundaries of the specified town (default).

label: buildingName
comment: (if applicable) In certain cases the physical location of the place of interest does not have a direct point of entry from the street, but may be located inside a larger structure such as a building, complex, office block, apartment, etc.

label: addressGeneral3
comment: (if applicable) Third line of a free form address.

label: type
comment: Type of street. Examples include: street, circle, boulevard, avenue, road, drive, etc.

label: addressGeneral2
comment: (if applicable) Second line of a free form address.

label: number
comment: Designator of the specific location on the street.

label: addressGeneral
comment: First line of a free form address or some additional address information (for example a mail stop).

label: prefix
comment: Prefix to the street name. For example: North, South, East, West.

label: section
comment: Town section. For example, it is common for there to be 36 sections per township.

label: stateOrProvince
comment: Name of the state or province.

label: code
comment: Town code.

label: country
comment: Name of the country.

label: name
comment: Town name.
